gomodel:SYNGO_4790  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: superresolution microscopy (3D-STORM) showed that both PK1 (Prickle1) and PK2 (Prickle2) were predominantly colocalized with the postsynaptic marker, PSD-95, but not with the presynaptic marker, Bassoon (Fig. 1A and movies S1 to S4).\n\n\"Although we were not able to pinpoint the exact information of how PK1 and PK2 are colocalized in synapses, we conclude that there is a considerable overlap of the distribution of PK1 and PK2 in synapses.\". Experimental description: All experiments were performed on mice. M&M: \"Dissociated hippocampal neurons were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) mouse hippocampi\"\n\nantibodies:\nanti-PK1 (Proteintech, 22589-1-AP)\nanti-PK2 (Millipore Sigma, MABN1529)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4790" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

